<s1 id=TourMainPanel>Tour of the Main Panel
	<idx>main panel<\idx>

The default main panel includes the following controls. Since it
can be customized, your Front Panel may contain additional
or different controls.

These terms are used to describe controls:
<lablist>
\Click\	What happens when you click the control.
\Drop\  What happens when you drop a file or folder icon on the control.
\Indicator\ What the image of the control represents.
<\lablist>

<newline>&empty;


	<idx>Clock control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPClockIcon><term nogloss>Clock<\term>
<newline>Indicator: Displays the current time.


	<idx>Date control<\idx>
	<idx>Calendar control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPSysdateIcon><term nogloss>Calendar<\term>
<newline>Click: Starts the Calendar application.
<newline>Indicator: Displays the current date. 



	<idx>File Manager control<\idx>
		<idx>Home control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPFileManagerIcon><term nogloss>File Manager&emdash;Home<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens a File Manager view of your home folder.
<newline>Drop: Opens a File Manager view of the dropped folder.

	<idx>Personal Applications control<\idx>
	<idx>Text Editor control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPpersonalAppsIcon><term nogloss>Text Editor&emdash;Personal
Applications<\term> 
<newline>Click: Starts the desktop Text Editor application.
<newline>Drop: Opens the dropped file in a new Text Editor window.
<newline>This control position is reserved for a personal application
of your choice.  You can put an application here by first installing the
application icon into the Personal Application subpanel, and then using
the control's pop-up menu to place that control in the main panel.

	<idx>Mailer control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPMailIcon><term nogloss>Mailer<\term>
<newline>Click: Starts the Mailer.
<newline>Drop: Opens the file's contents in Mailer's Compose window.
<newline>Indicator: Indicates arrival of new mail.

	<idx>Lock control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPLockIcon><term nogloss>Lock<\term>
<newline>Click: Locks your workstation, preventing unauthorized input.


	<idx>Workspace switch<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPWorkspaceSwitchIcon><term nogloss>Workspace
switch<\term>.
<newline>Click: Displays other workspaces. 

	<idx>Busy light<\idx>
	<idx>Progress light<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPProgressLight><term nogloss>Busy Light<\term>
<newline>Indicator: Blinks when the system is running an action.


	<idx>Exit control<\idx>
	<idx>Logout control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPExitIcon><term nogloss>Exit<\term>
<newline>Click: Logs you out of the current session.


	<idx>Printer control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPPrinterIcon><term nogloss>Default Printer<\term>
<newline>Click: Displays the status of the default printer, lets you cancel
print jobs on that printer.
<newline>Drop: Prints the file on the default printer.


	<idx>Style Manager control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPStyleManagerIcon><term nogloss>Style Manager<\term>
<newline>Click: Starts the Style Manager application. If the application is
already running, its window is raised to the top of the window stack.

	<idx>Application Manager control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPAppManagerIcon><term nogloss>Application Manager<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens an Application Manager window.


	<idx>Help Manager control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPHelpmgrIcon><term nogloss>Help Manager<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens a Help Viewer window displaying the top level of help
information.

	<idx>Trash Can control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPTrashIcon><term nogloss>Trash Can<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens the Trash Can window.
<newline>Drop: Moves the file or folder to the Trash Can.

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref TourSubpanels>
<\list>


<s1 id=TourSubpanels>Tour of the Subpanels
	<idx>subpanels<\idx>

The default Front Panel includes these subpanels. Since it
can be customized, your Front Panel may contain additional
subpanels, and the subpanels may contain additional or different controls. 

These terms are used to describe controls:
<lablist>
\Click\	What happens when you click the control.
\Drop\  What happens when you drop a file or folder icon on the control.
\Indicator\ What the image of the control represents.
<\lablist>

<procedure>In All Subpanels

	<idx>Install Icon control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPControlInstallIcon><term nogloss>Install Icon<\term>
<newline>Drop: Creates a control based on the dropped file, folder, or
action icon, and installs the control in the subpanel. 


<procedure>Folders Subpanel
	<idx>File Manager Subpanel<\idx>
	<idx>Folders Subpanel<\idx>


Use the Folders Subpanel for files and folders you use frequently. 
Install files and folders into the subpanel by dragging their icons from the
File Manager to the Install Icon control.


<p indent gentity=FPFileManagerIcon><term nogloss><newline>File Manager&emdash;Home<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens a File Manager view of your home folder.
<newline>Drop: Opens a File Manager view of the dropped folder.
<newline>This control is a duplicate of the control in the main panel.


<idx>Personal Bookmarks<\idx>
<p indent gentity=SDturlfile><term nogloss>Personal Bookmarks<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens your Personal Bookmarks folder displaying bookmarks.
<newline>Drop: Dropping text onto the control creates a file with a .url extension in the Personal Bookmarks folder.

 

<idx>Open Floppy action<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPRMOpenFloppyIcon><term nogloss>Open Floppy<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens a File Manager view of the floppy diskette 
in the floppy diskette drive. If you have multiple floppy drives, 
Open Floppy opens a File Manager view for each readable floppy diskette 
you have inserted.


<idx>Open CD-ROM action<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPRMOpenCDROMIcon><term nogloss>Open CD-ROM<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens a File Manager view of the  <newline>CD-ROM 
in the CD-ROM drive. If you have multiple CD-ROM drives, Open CD-ROM 
opens a File Manager view for each readable CD-ROM you have inserted.


<procedure>Personal Applications Subpanel
	<idx>Personal Applications Subpanel<\idx>

Use the Personal Applications subpanel for applications you use frequently.
Install applications into the subpanel by dragging their icons from the
Application Manager to the Install Icon control.

<p indent gentity=FPEditorIcon><term nogloss>Text Editor--Personal
Applications<\term>. 
<newline>Click: Starts the desktop Text Editor application.
<newline>Drop: Opens the dropped file in a new Text Editor window.
<newline>This control is duplicate of the control in the main panel.

	<idx>Terminal control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPTerminalIcon><term nogloss>Terminal<\term>
<newline>Click: Starts a terminal emulator.


<idx>Web Browser control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=SDtwebbr><term nogloss>Web Browser<\term>
<newline>Click: Starts your default web browser.
<newline>Drop: Opens the dropped file in your default web browser.


<procedure>Personal Printers Subpanel
	<idx>Personal Printers Subpanel<\idx>


Use the Personal Printers Subpanel for printers you use frequently.
Install printers into the subpanel by dragging them from the Printers
application group to the Install Icon control.


<p indent gentity=FPSmallPrinterIcon><term nogloss>Default Printer<\term>
<newline>Click: Displays the status of the default printer; you can cancel
print jobs on that printer.
<newline>Drop: Prints the file on the default printer.
<newline>This control is a duplicate of the control in the main panel.

	<idx>Print Manager control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPPrintMgrIcon><term nogloss>Print Manager<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens the Print Manager window.
<newline>Drop: Prints the file on the default printer.



<procedure>Applications Subpanel
	<idx>Help Subpanel<\idx>

<idx>Applications control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=Dtapps><term nogloss>Applications<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens an Application Manager window displaying the top level 
folders.
<newline>This control is a duplicate of the control in the main panel.

<idx>Desktop_Apps control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=Dtadskt><term nogloss>Desktop_Apps<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens the Desktop_Apps folder.


<idx>Desktop_Controls control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=SDtactrls><term nogloss>Desktop_Controls<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens the Desktop_Controls folder.


<idx>Information control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=Dtainfo><term nogloss>Information<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens the Information folder.






<procedure>Help Subpanel
	<idx>Help Subpanel<\idx>

	<idx>Help Manager control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPSmallHelp><term nogloss>Help Manager<\term>
<newline>Click: Opens a Help Viewer window displaying the top level of help
information.
<newline>This control is a duplicate of the control in the main panel.

	<idx>Desktop Introduction control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPHelpIntro><term nogloss>Desktop Introduction<\term>
<newline>Click: Displays the help volume "Introducing the Desktop."

	<idx>Front Panel Help control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPHelpOnFrontPanelIcon><term nogloss>Front Panel
Help<\term>
<newline>Click: Displays the Front Panel help volume.

	<idx>On-Item Help control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPOnItemFrontPanelHelp><term nogloss>On-Item Help<\term>
<newline>Click: Provides on-item help for the Front Panel. Click this
control, then click the control on which you want help.

	<idx>AnswerBook2 control<\idx>
<p indent gentity=FPOnItemOWAnswerBookIcon><term nogloss>AnswerBook2<\term>
<newline>Click: Starts the AnswerBook2 viewer.

