<s1 id=ChooseFrontPanelControlTA> To Activate a Front Panel Control
	<idx>choosing:Front Panel control<\idx>
	<idx>Front Panel:control, choosing<\idx>
	<idx>control:Front Panel<\idx>

<list bullet>
<item> Click the control.
<\list>

Some controls do not have a click action&emdash;for example, the clock control
and busy indicator.


<s1 id=ToDisplaySubpanel>To Open and Close Subpanels
	<idx>subpanel:opening<\idx>
	<idx>subpanel:closing<\idx>

Initially, the Text Editor, Printer, and Help Manager controls have
subpanels. You can add subpanels to other controls. See <xref AddSubpanel>.

<procedure> To Open a Subpanel
<list bullet>
<item> Click the arrow button above the control.
<\list>

<figure nonumber entity=FPSubpanelArrowButton>
<\figure>

<procedure>To Close a Subpanel

<note>
If you have not moved a subpanel from its initial position, it closes
automatically when you choose a control. 
<\note>

<list bullet>
<item> Click the down arrow at the bottom of the subpanel.
<item> !!Or!!, choose Close from the subpanel's Window menu.
<\list>

<figure nonumber entity=FPCloseSubpanel>
<\figure>


